#: Game.Levels.PsetFinset
msgid "# Problem Set: Finsets\n"
"\n"
"You've completed three lecture worlds on finsets:\n"
"- **FinsetBasics**: membership, range, insert, singleton, nonempty\n"
"- **FinsetOperations**: union, intersection, sdiff, filter, subset, ext, by_contra\n"
"- **FinsetImage**: image, forward/backward membership, cardinality, injectivity\n"
"\n"
"Now apply these skills to **fresh problems** with sparser hints and\n"
"no new definitions. One new bridge fact вҖ” В§0 вҖ”\n"
"connects range to cardinality.\n"
"\n"
"**Note on disabled tactics**: В§1 is disabled throughout this\n"
"pset. Because В§2 uses the same В§3 tactic internally,\n"
"it is also unavailable here. You learned В§4 as a targeted\n"
"simplification tool in FinsetOperations вҖ” and it IS a good tool.\n"
"But this pset is specifically testing whether you can construct\n"
"В§5 chains from individual lemma names. The skill being assessed\n"
"is: given a membership goal, can you identify and apply the correct\n"
"sequence of В§6, В§7, etc.\n"
"without automation choosing the lemmas for you? В§8 will be\n"
"available again in later worlds. Tactics like В§9, В§10,\n"
"and В§11 are also disabled вҖ” you're expected to handle negations\n"
"with В§12 and В§13, and arithmetic with В§14."
msgstr ""

#. В§0: $$|f(S)| = |S| \\iff f \\text{ is injective on } S$$
#. В§1: $\\Leftarrow$
#. В§2: `card_image_of_injective`
#. В§3: $\\Rightarrow$
#. В§4: $n \\mapsto \\lfloor n/2 \\rfloor$
#. В§5: $\\mathbb{N}$
#. В§6: $\\mathbb{N}$
#. В§7: $n+1$
#. В§8: $n$
#. В§9: `Fintype.card_congr`
#. В§10: `Finset`
#. В§11: `Fintype`
#. В§12: $|f(S)| = |S|$
#. В§13: $\\Rightarrow$
#. В§14: `card_image_iff`
#: Game.Levels.FinsetImage.L19_CardPreservationConverse
msgid "This is the **fundamental equivalence** of finite-set images:\n"
"\n"
"В§0\n"
"\n"
"The forward direction (В§1) is Level 13's\n"
"В§2. The backward direction (В§3)\n"
"is the converse you just used.\n"
"\n"
"This equivalence is **unique to finite sets** вҖ” for infinite sets,\n"
"a function can preserve 'size' (cardinality) while not being\n"
"injective (e.g., В§4 maps В§5\n"
"onto В§6 but is not injective).\n"
"\n"
"The equivalence connects several themes:\n"
"- **Pigeonhole principle** (PsetFin): if you map В§7 pigeons\n"
"  into В§8 holes, two must collide вҖ” contrapositive of the\n"
"  converse direction\n"
"- **Counting arguments**: size preservation is a test for\n"
"  injectivity without checking every pair\n"
"- **Finite type theory**: В§9 will generalize\n"
"  this from В§10 to В§11\n"
"\n"
"**Transferable strategy вҖ” counting proves injectivity**: When you\n"
"need to show a function is injective on a finite set, you have\n"
"two approaches: (1) check every pair of inputs (often tedious),\n"
"or (2) count the image and show В§12. Approach (2)\n"
"is often dramatically easier вҖ” you'll see it in action next level.\n"
"\n"
"In the next level, you'll see this equivalence in action: using\n"
"cardinality to prove injectivity for a function where checking\n"
"every pair directly would be tedious. The backward direction\n"
"(В§13) is especially powerful: it lets you prove\n"
"injectivity by counting, avoiding the need to check every pair\n"
"of inputs.\n"
"\n"
"You'll use В§14 again in the Cardinality world,\n"
"where counting arguments routinely convert between cardinality\n"
"equations and injectivity statements."
msgstr ""

