#: Game.Levels.AbstractionLadder.L09_MeetTheMultiset
msgid "# Climbing the Ladder: List вҶ’ Multiset\n"
"\n"
"A В§0 is a **list quotiented by permutation**. Two lists\n"
"that are permutations of each other become the *same* multiset.\n"
"\n"
"The coercion В§1 (or В§2) sends a В§3 to the\n"
"corresponding В§4. The key bridge lemma is:\n"
"\n"
"В§5\n"
"\n"
"In other words: two lists give the same multiset **if and only if**\n"
"they are permutations of each other. This is exactly what 'quotient\n"
"by permutation' means.\n"
"\n"
"**What's lost**: Order. В§6 and В§7 are different\n"
"lists but the same multiset.\n"
"\n"
"**What's kept**: Multiplicities. A multiset remembers *how many* of\n"
"each element it contains.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that В§8 and В§9 give the same\n"
"multiset. You'll need to rewrite with В§10 and then\n"
"prove the permutation вҖ” using the swap-chaining technique from L07.\n"
"\n"
"**Tip**: If term-mode В§11 feels hard to type in one go, you can\n"
"use В§12 for intermediate feedback."
msgstr ""

