#: Game.Levels.FinsetInduction
msgid "# Finset Induction\n"
"\n"
"You now know how to manipulate sums and products algebraically вҖ”\n"
"splitting summands, factoring, swapping order, peeling terms off\n"
"ranges. But all of those tools work by applying *existing* identities.\n"
"\n"
"What if you need to prove a sum or product identity that isn't in\n"
"the library?\n"
"\n"
"**Finset induction** is the answer. Just as you prove statements\n"
"about natural numbers by induction on В§0 (base case В§1, step\n"
"В§2), you can prove statements about finsets by induction\n"
"on В§3:\n"
"\n"
"- **Base case**: prove the statement for В§4\n"
"- **Inductive step**: given a finset В§5 and a fresh element\n"
"  В§6, assume the statement holds for В§7 and prove it for\n"
"  В§8\n"
"\n"
"The inductive step always follows the same **collect-and-close**\n"
"pattern:\n"
"1. **Collect** вҖ” peel with В§9 (or В§10),\n"
"   substitute the IH, peel cardinalities if needed\n"
"2. **Close** вҖ” finish the arithmetic with В§11 or В§12\n"
"\n"
"This world teaches the complete induction workflow for both sums\n"
"and products over arbitrary finsets.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: В§13, В§14 from BigOpIntro,\n"
"В§15 from BigOpAlgebra, and В§16 from MeetFin."
msgstr ""

