#: Game.Levels.Fintype.L11_BijectiveCounting
msgid "# Counting via Equivalence\n"
"\n"
"If two types В§0 and В§1 are in bijection вҖ” meaning there exists an\n"
"В§2 (written В§3, typed В§4) вҖ” then they must have the\n"
"same number of elements. The theorem В§5 captures this:\n"
"\n"
"В§6\n"
"\n"
"Given an equivalence В§7, the proof В§8\n"
"produces the equation В§9.\n"
"\n"
"An В§10 is a bijection with four fields: the forward map (В§11),\n"
"the inverse map (В§12), and proofs that they compose to the\n"
"identity in both directions (В§13, В§14). Think of\n"
"В§15 as saying: there's a perfect pairing between the elements\n"
"of В§16 and the elements of В§17.\n"
"\n"
"This is the formal version of **bijective counting**: to count the\n"
"elements of a complicated type, find a bijection to a simpler type\n"
"and count that instead.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Given an equivalence В§18, prove that\n"
"В§19 has 6 elements. Use В§20 to transfer the\n"
"cardinality, then В§21 to evaluate."
