#: Game.Levels.FinNavigation
msgid "# Navigating Fin\n"
"\n"
"You've learned to construct and compare elements of В§0. Now\n"
"you'll learn to *navigate* within В§1 вҖ” accessing specific\n"
"landmark elements and moving between В§2 and В§3.\n"
"\n"
"Three functions form the navigation toolkit:\n"
"\n"
"**В§4** вҖ” the maximum element of В§5, with\n"
"value В§6. It's the boundary element, sitting at the top.\n"
"\n"
"**В§7** вҖ” embeds В§8 into В§9 by keeping\n"
"the same value but relaxing the bound. If В§10 has value\n"
"В§11, then В§12 also has value В§13.\n"
"\n"
"**В§14** вҖ” moves forward: if В§15 has value В§16,\n"
"then В§17 has value В§18.\n"
"\n"
"Both В§19 and В§20 send В§21 вҖ” they\n"
"increase the type's size by 1 вҖ” but they do different things to\n"
"the value: В§22 preserves it, В§23 increments it.\n"
"\n"
"(This is why В§24 starts at 0: the embedding В§25\n"
"preserves values exactly, and В§26 increments by exactly 1. With\n"
"1-indexing, these clean relationships would need offsets.)\n"
"\n"
"The central insight of this world: В§27 has **two**\n"
"decompositions:\n"
"- Every element is either В§28 or В§29\n"
"  for some В§30 (**castSucc/last**)\n"
"- Every element is either В§31 or В§32\n"
"  for some В§33 (**0/succ**)\n"
"\n"
"These dual decompositions will power the two ways to build\n"
"tuples in the next world.\n"
"\n"
"In this world, you'll learn to:\n"
"- Compute the value of В§34, В§35, and В§36 using their\n"
"  val lemmas\n"
"- Prove that В§37 never reaches В§38 (and В§39 never\n"
"  reaches В§40)\n"
"- Prove that both В§41 and В§42 are injective\n"
"- Prove both the castSucc/last and 0/succ decompositions\n"
"- Prove that В§43 hits every non-last element (surjectivity)\n"
"- Combine all of this in the boss"
msgstr ""

