#: Game.Levels.FinsetBasics
msgid "# Finset Basics: Finite Sets\n"
"\n"
"In Phase 1, you learned about В§0 вҖ” a finite *index type* where\n"
"each element is a number with a bound proof. Functions В§1\n"
"gave you *ordered tuples*: data accessed by position.\n"
"\n"
"But not everything in mathematics has a natural ordering. The set of\n"
"prime divisors of 30 is В§2 вҖ” there's no reason 2 should\n"
"come 'first'. The elements of a group satisfying some property form a\n"
"*collection defined by membership*, not by position.\n"
"\n"
"This is where В§3 comes in. A В§4 is an **unordered finite\n"
"collection** of elements from В§5, with no duplicates and decidable\n"
"membership. Think of it as a mathematical finite set, formalized.\n"
"\n"
"The key operations:\n"
"- **Literal notation**: В§6 builds a concrete finset\n"
"- **В§7**: the empty finset\n"
"- **В§8**: add an element (no-op if already present)\n"
"- **В§9**: the set В§10\n"
"\n"
"The key proof move: to show В§11, unfold the set structure using\n"
"*membership lemmas* (В§12, В§13,\n"
"В§14) until the goal reduces to something В§15 or\n"
"В§16 can close.\n"
"\n"
"The bridge from Phase 1: В§17 contains exactly the same\n"
"elements as В§18 вҖ” the numbers В§19 through В§20. Where В§21\n"
"gave you *indexed access* (В§22 for В§23), В§24\n"
"gives you *membership* (В§25). Same elements,\n"
"different interface.\n"
"\n"
"In this world you'll learn to prove membership, non-membership,\n"
"and basic structural facts about finsets. The boss at the end\n"
"combines all these moves."
msgstr ""

