"You'll use this pattern repeatedly вҖ” whenever you need to prove two В§2\n"
"elements are equal, reduce it to their values.\n"
"\n"
"The converse direction is trivial: if В§3 then certainly\n"
"В§4 (applying a function preserves equality). You'll\n"
"practice this direction in the next level.\n"
"\n"
"In plain mathematics, this is the obvious fact that elements of\n"
"В§5 are just numbers, and two numbers are equal\n"
"when they're the same number. So why does Lean need a lemma for this?\n"
"\n"
"Because В§6 is a **subtype** вҖ” a wrapper around a natural number\n"
"and a proof. An element В§7 is really В§8:\n"
"a number *packaged with* a proof that it's in range. Lean's type\n"
"system distinguishes between the *wrapper* В§9 and the *contained\n"
"value* В§10. Two wrappers could in principle differ (maybe the\n"
"proofs are different?) even if the values match. В§11 says:\n"
"no, the proof component doesn't matter вҖ” equality of the wrapper\n"
"is determined entirely by equality of the contained value. (You'll\n"
