#: Game.Levels.Cardinality.L24_Capstone
msgid "# The Capstone Theorem\n"
"\n"
"You've assembled all the pieces. Now for the punchline.\n"
"\n"
"For finite types, **injectivity implies surjectivity**. If\n"
"В§0 is injective (different inputs give different\n"
"outputs), then В§1 is also surjective (every output is hit).\n"
"\n"
"Why? The image В§2 satisfies:\n"
"- It has В§3 elements (by В§4, since В§5 is injective)\n"
"- It is a subset of В§6 (by В§7, since everything\n"
"  lives in the universe)\n"
"\n"
"A subset with the same number of elements as the whole must BE the\n"
"whole. This is В§8:\n"
"\n"
"В§9\n"
"\n"
"If a subset is at least as large as its superset, they're equal.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that if В§10 is injective, then\n"
"the image of В§11 under В§12 equals В§13 вҖ” meaning В§14 hits every\n"
"element."
msgstr ""

