#: Game.Levels.AbstractionLadder.L06_Permutations
msgid "# Lists Are Ordered вҖ” Permutations Ignore Order\n"
"\n"
"Two lists with the same elements in different orders are **not** equal:\n"
"В§0. Order is part of a list's identity.\n"
"\n"
"But sometimes we want to say 'these lists have the same elements,\n"
"just rearranged.' That's В§1 вҖ” the permutation relation.\n"
"\n"
"We write В§2 (or В§3) to mean В§4 is a permutation\n"
"of В§5.\n"
"\n"
"The key building blocks:\n"
"\n"
"- **В§6** вҖ” swapping two adjacent elements gives\n"
"  a permutation: В§7\n"
"- **В§8** вҖ” if В§9, then В§10\n"
"  (prepending the same element preserves the permutation)\n"
"- **В§11** вҖ” if В§12 and В§13,\n"
"  then В§14 (chain permutations)\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that В§15 is a permutation of В§16.\n"
"This is a single swap of the first two elements."
