#: Game.Levels.FinsetBasics.L01_WhatIsAFinset
msgid "# What is a Finset?\n"
"\n"
"A В§0 is a finite set of elements from type В§1. Unlike tuples\n"
"(В§2), finsets are **unordered** and have **no duplicates**.\n"
"\n"
"You can write concrete finsets using literal notation:\n"
"- В§3 вҖ” a finset of three natural numbers\n"
"- В§4 вҖ” a finset of booleans\n"
"\n"
"**Why DecidableEq?** Finsets require В§5 вҖ” Lean must be\n"
"able to decide whether two elements are equal. Why? Because maintaining\n"
"'no duplicates' requires checking whether an inserted element is already\n"
"present. If you can't decide В§6, you can't check for duplicates.\n"
"This is why В§7 doesn't exist in general вҖ” real number equality\n"
"isn't decidable.\n"
"\n"
"Under the hood, В§8 is sugar for nested В§9 calls:\n"
"В§10\n"
"\n"
"where В§11 is a *singleton* вҖ” a set with exactly one element.\n"
"\n"
"The fundamental question for any set: **is this element a member?**\n"
"\n"
"The key lemma is В§12:\n"
"В§13\n"
"\n"
"In words: В§14 is in В§15 if either В§16 (it's the inserted\n"
"element) or В§17 was already in В§18.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that В§19.\n"
"\n"
"Use В§20 to unfold the membership test. Since\n"
"В§21 is В§22, this rewrites the goal to\n"
"В§23. Then choose the left branch with В§24 and\n"
"close with В§25."
msgstr ""

