#: Game.Levels.FinsetImage.L23_Boss
msgid "Congratulations вҖ” you've completed **Finset Image**!\n"
"\n"
"You mastered four core move families:\n"
"\n"
"**1. Forward membership** (witness construction):\n"
"- В§0\n"
"- Choose В§1 by solving В§2\n"
"\n"
"**2. Backward extraction** (witness destruction):\n"
"- В§3\n"
"- Used for non-membership proofs, subset proofs, and re-use\n"
"\n"
"**3. Cardinality bounds**:\n"
"- В§4: В§5 (always)\n"
"- В§6: В§7 (when В§8 is injective)\n"
"- В§9: В§10 is injective on В§11\n"
"- Injectivity proof: В§12\n"
"\n"
"**4. Image algebra**:\n"
"- Image distributes over union: В§13\n"
"- Image of intersection: В§14\n"
"  (equality under injectivity)\n"
"- Image of singleton: В§15\n"
"\n"
"| Theorem | What it says |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| В§16 | В§17 |\n"
"| В§18 | В§19 |\n"
"| В§20 | injective В§21 implies В§22 |\n"
"| В§23 | В§24 |\n"
"\n"
"**Injectivity vs. surjectivity**: This world focused on\n"
"*injectivity* вҖ” does В§25 preserve distinctness? The dual question\n"
"is *surjectivity* вҖ” does В§26 cover the target? When does\n"
"В§27 for a target set В§28? Cardinality will\n"
"connect the two: counting arguments show that injectivity between\n"
"same-size sets *implies* surjectivity. The pigeonhole principle is\n"
"a non-surjectivity result in disguise.\n"
"\n"
"**The dual operation**: Everything in this world went forward вҖ”\n"
"given a source set В§29, compute В§30. The dual question goes\n"
"backward: given a target set В§31, which elements of the domain\n"
"map *into* В§32? That's В§33 вҖ” the finset version of\n"
"the preimage. It appears in later worlds when you need to reason\n"
"about which inputs produce a desired output.\n"
"\n"
"**What's next**: Problem Set Finset will test these skills on fresh\n"
"problems without scaffolding."
msgstr ""

