msgid "You just proved injectivity **without checking a single pair**.\n"
"Instead of showing В§0 for all\n"
"В§1, you showed В§2 and let\n"
"В§3 do the rest.\n"
"\n"
"This is the counting-proves-injectivity technique:\n"
"1. В§4 вҖ” convert to cardinality\n"
"2. В§5 (or В§6) вҖ” verify computationally\n"
"\n"
"The technique works whenever the domain is a concrete finset.\n"
"For abstract finsets, you'd need to compute or bound the\n"
"cardinality by other means.\n"
"\n"
"This is the **payoff** of the cardinality arc (Levels 12-18):\n"
"cardinality isn't just a number вҖ” it's a proof technique. Knowing\n"
"В§7 tells you the function has no collisions, which is\n"
"the *definition* of injectivity.\n"
"\n"
"**Name this strategy**: 'counting proves injectivity.' It appears\n"
"throughout combinatorics вҖ” whenever you can count the image and\n"
"confirm no elements were lost, you've proved injectivity without\n"
"examining a single pair. The pattern is always the same:\n"
"1. В§8 вҖ” convert to cardinality\n"
"2. Compute or bound the image size\n"
"3. Conclude injectivity\n"
"\n"
"**The full circle**: You now have the complete equivalence for finite\n"
"sets: a function is injective on В§9 if and only if it preserves\n"
"cardinality (В§10). Level 15 proved the forward direction\n"
"(В§11: injective implies card preserved), Level 17\n"
"gave the biconditional (В§12), and this level used the\n"
"reverse direction as a proof technique. For finite sets, counting IS\n"
"a proof of injectivity.\n"
"\n"
"Next: a practice level for the В§13 tactic applied to injectivity\n"
"proofs, then the boss."
msgstr ""

