#: Game.Levels.CountingTypes.L05_FallingFactorials
msgid "В§0\n"
"\n"
"The falling factorial counts **ordered selections without replacement**:\n"
"choosing В§1 items from В§2 where order matters and no item is repeated.\n"
"\n"
"| Unfolding step | Result |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| В§3 | concrete: В§4 |\n"
"| В§5 (k=2) | В§6 |\n"
"| В§7 (k=1) | В§8 |\n"
"| В§9 (k=0) | В§10 |\n"
"| В§11 | В§12 |\n"
"\n"
"**Note on factor order**: The factors appear as В§13 (ascending), not\n"
"В§14 (descending). This is because В§15 peels off\n"
"В§16 starting from the largest В§17, so the recursion works bottom-up\n"
"even though the mathematical narrative goes top-down. The product is the\n"
"same either way.\n"
"\n"
"Special cases:\n"
"- В§18 (empty selection)\n"
"- В§19 (one choice)\n"
"- В§20 (all items = permutation)\n"
"\n"
"**Boundary case**: When В§21, the falling factorial is zero:\n"
"В§22. You can't select more items than exist without\n"
"replacement. This is the counting-theoretic version of the pigeonhole\n"
"principle вҖ” if you have more pigeons than holes, no injection exists."
msgstr ""

