#: Game.Levels.MeetFin.L01_WhatIsFin
msgid "# What is В§0?\n"
"\n"
"In mathematics, we often work with finite index sets like\n"
"В§1 вҖ” the first В§2 natural numbers.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean 4, this is captured by the type В§3. An element of В§4\n"
"is a natural number В§5 **together with a proof** that В§6.\n"
"\n"
"More precisely:\n"
"В§7\n"
"\n"
"**Why not just use В§8?** If you index a length-5 vector with a plain\n"
"natural number, nothing stops you from using В§9 вҖ” the type checker\n"
"can't tell it's out of bounds. With В§10, the bound is part of the\n"
"type: you literally *cannot construct* an element unless you prove it's\n"
"in range. The type system enforces the constraint for you.\n"
"\n"
"You might wonder why В§11 starts at 0 rather than 1.\n"
"Zero-indexing means the values of В§12 are exactly the natural\n"
"numbers less than В§13, which aligns with how Lean indexes lists and\n"
"arrays. It also means В§14 has a natural 'zero' element when\n"
"В§15.\n"
"\n"
"This is an example of a *subtype* вҖ” a type carved out of a larger type\n"
"by a predicate. В§16 is the subtype В§17.\n"
"\n"
"To construct an element of В§18, use the **anonymous constructor**\n"
"В§19, where:\n"
"- В§20 is the natural number\n"
"- В§21 shows В§22\n"
"\n"
"For the proof part, the В§23 tactic handles routine arithmetic\n"
"goals like В§24.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Construct any element of В§25. There are five to\n"
"choose from: В§26.\n"
"\n"
"Try В§27.\n"
"\n"
"*Notation*: type В§28 as В§29 and В§30 as В§31.\n"
"\n"
"**Important**: Lean happens to accept В§32 for this level\n"
"because it can figure out the bound automatically when it's a\n"
"concrete number like В§33. But this shortcut will **stop working**\n"
"starting at Level 12, when the bound becomes a variable В§34.\n"
"Practice В§35 now вҖ” it's the pattern that always works."
msgstr ""

