#: Game.Levels.MeetFin.L17_TwoElements
msgid "You've just performed **exhaustive case analysis** on В§0.\n"
"\n"
"The strategy вҖ” which we'll call **Fin case analysis** вҖ” is:\n"
"1. **Destructure** the В§1 element: В§2 (Level 16)\n"
"2. **Case-split** on the natural number: В§3\n"
"3. **Handle** each case: valid cases with В§4/В§5 + В§6,\n"
"   impossible cases with В§7 + В§8\n"
"\n"
"**Why does this work?** Exhaustive case analysis on В§9 terminates\n"
"because В§10 bounds the natural number. Each В§11 step peels\n"
"off one possible value (0, then 1, then 2, ...), and the В§12\n"
"bound ensures that after В§13 valid cases, the remaining case is\n"
"impossible вҖ” the value would need to be вүҘ В§14, contradicting В§15.\n"
"This is the **Fin contradiction pattern** from Level 13 applied to the\n"
"impossible branch. This termination is what makes В§16 a *finite*\n"
"type in a proof-relevant sense: you can enumerate all elements and\n"
"handle each one. This idea will be formalized as В§17 in a later\n"
"world.\n"
"\n"
"This strategy works for any В§18 by nesting enough В§19 on the\n"
"natural number. But imagine doing this for В§20: you'd need 100\n"
"branches, 99 of which are contradiction proofs. The В§21 tactic\n"
"(currently disabled) automates all of this вҖ” it performs the case split\n"
"and handles the impossible branches automatically. You'll unlock it\n"
"later.\n"
"\n"
"Fun fact: В§22 is equivalent to В§23 вҖ” both have exactly two\n"
"elements. Where В§24 has В§25 and В§26, В§27 has В§28 and В§29.\n"
"\n"
"**A note on В§30**: You used В§31 here for a *bound violation*\n"
"in case analysis вҖ” the value was too large for the bound. This is a\n"
"general tool you'll use in later worlds whenever you have contradictory\n"
"hypotheses. In the next level, you'll practice case analysis on В§32,\n"
"and after that you'll learn a different pattern (В§33)\n"
"for when *constructors themselves* don't match (like В§34)."
msgstr ""

