msgid "Congratulations! You proved:\n"
"В§0\n"
"\n"
"**Skills integrated in this boss**:\n"
"1. В§1 вҖ” natural number induction\n"
"2. В§2 вҖ” boundary value C(2, 2) = 1 (Level 1)\n"
"3. В§3 вҖ” Pascal's identity (Level 3)\n"
"4. В§4 вҖ” C(n, 1) = n (Level 2)\n"
"5. В§5 вҖ” distributing multiplication\n"
"6. В§6 вҖ” the induction hypothesis\n"
"7. В§7 вҖ” closing the polynomial identity\n"
"\n"
"**The pattern**: Peel with Pascal, simplify leaves with the boundary\n"
"theorems, distribute, substitute the IH, and close with В§8. This\n"
"is the **collect-and-close** skeleton (from FinsetInduction): bring\n"
"structural facts into context (here via В§9), then close with an\n"
"algebraic tactic (В§10). The same skeleton appears in\n"
"SummationFormulas, now applied to binomial coefficients.\n"
"\n"
"**The formula**: В§11 counts the number of\n"
"2-element subsets вҖ” equivalently, the number of handshakes among\n"
"В§12 people. These are the **triangular numbers**: В§13\n"
"\n"
"The triangular numbers are also the partial sums В§14 from the SummationFormulas world. In Level 14, you proved this\n"
"connection formally: В§15. And in Level 15,\n"
"you proved the full generalization вҖ” the **hockey stick identity**:\n"
"В§16.\n"
"\n"
"The binomial coefficient В§17 also counts the 2-element\n"
"subsets of an В§18-element set вҖ” a connection you'll explore in the\n"
"**Powerset** world.\n"
"\n"
"The binomial coefficients also give their name to the **binomial theorem**:\n"
"В§19\n"
"The entries of row В§20 of Pascal's triangle are exactly the coefficients\n"
"in the expansion of В§21 вҖ” which is why they are called *binomial*\n"
"coefficients. Setting В§22 gives В§23:\n"
"the sum of each row is a power of В§24. You'll prove this in the\n"
"BinomialTheorem world."
msgstr ""

