#: Game.Levels.AbstractionLadder.L05_DuplicateElements
msgid "# Lists Can Have Duplicates\n"
"\n"
"Before we move to permutations, let's observe something important:\n"
"**lists can contain duplicate elements**.\n"
"\n"
"Consider a list В§0 where element В§1 already appears (В§2).\n"
"If you prepend В§3 to В§4 with В§5, the resulting list has\n"
"В§6 appearing at least twice вҖ” once at the head, and at least once\n"
"in the tail.\n"
"\n"
"This is a preview of the abstraction ladder:\n"
"\n"
"| Layer | Duplicates? | Count measure |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| **List** | yes | В§7 counts all entries |\n"
"| **Multiset** | yes | В§8 counts all entries |\n"
"| **Finset** | no | В§9 counts distinct elements |\n"
"\n"
"Lists and multisets keep every copy. Finsets discard duplicates,\n"
"so their В§10 can be strictly smaller than the list В§11.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Given a list В§12 of length 1 and an element В§13\n"
"that belongs to В§14, compute the length of В§15.\n"
"\n"
"Since В§16, the list В§17 contains В§18 at least twice.\n"
"But В§19 counts all entries вҖ” duplicates included. You'll peel\n"
"off each В§20 with В§21 and close with the hypothesis."
msgstr ""

