#: Game.Levels.FinNavigation.L16_Boss
msgid "Congratulations вҖ” you've completed **Fin Navigation**!\n"
"\n"
"**The Decomposition** (Part 1): Every element of В§0 is\n"
"either В§1 or В§2 for some В§3. This\n"
"is the В§4 analog of: every natural number В§5 either\n"
"equals В§6 or is strictly less than В§7.\n"
"\n"
"Combined with the **separation fact** from Level 7 вҖ” that no\n"
"В§8 image equals В§9 вҖ” this gives you a **disjoint\n"
"decomposition**: В§10 is the disjoint union of the\n"
"В§11 images (values В§12) and the singleton\n"
"В§13 (value В§14). Part 1 gives **exhaustion** (every\n"
"element falls into one of the two sets), and Level 7 gives\n"
"**disjointness** (no element falls into both). Together:\n"
"В§15, disjointly.\n"
"\n"
"**Connection to induction**: This decomposition is the structural\n"
"basis for **induction on Fin types**, just as В§16\n"
"is the basis for induction on natural numbers. To prove a property\n"
"holds for all elements of В§17, you can:\n"
"1. Handle В§18 as a base-like case\n"
"2. Handle В§19 by reducing to В§20 (the inductive step)\n"
"\n"
"You've already proved every ingredient for showing\n"
"В§21 by induction: В§22 (Fin 0 is empty,\n"
"MeetFin L13), the decomposition В§23\n"
"(disjointly), and injectivity of castSucc (Level 8). The\n"
"formal proof will appear in the Cardinality world вҖ” but the\n"
"mathematical content is already in your hands.\n"
"\n"
"There are actually *two* decompositions вҖ” the **castSucc/last**\n"
"decomposition you just proved, and the **0/succ** decomposition\n"
"from Level 10 (every element is either В§24 or В§25). Both\n"
"are structural tools for В§26. When you build tuples in the\n"
"next world: В§27 (adding at the back) uses the castSucc/last\n"
"decomposition, while В§28 (adding at the front) uses the\n"
"0/succ decomposition.\n"
"\n"
"**Succ Injectivity** (Part 2): The value reasoning pattern вҖ”\n"
"convert to values, simplify, omega вҖ” handles injectivity\n"
"automatically. This property вҖ” equal outputs imply equal inputs вҖ”\n"
"is called **injectivity**. In Lean, В§29 means\n"
"В§30. You just proved\n"
"В§31 (in Level 8) and\n"
"В§32 (in Level 9). You'll use injectivity\n"
"formally in the FinsetImage world.\n"
"\n"
"Here's your navigation toolkit:\n"
"\n"
"| Tool | What it does | Val lemma |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| В§33 | Maximum element of В§34 | В§35 |\n"
"| В§36 | Embed into larger type (same value) | В§37 |\n"
"| В§38 | Move forward by 1 | В§39 |\n"
"\n"
"And the proof recipes:\n"
"\n"
"| Recipe | Pattern |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| Compare В§40 values | val lemmas + В§41 |\n"
"| Prove В§42 equality | В§43 + val lemmas |\n"
"| Prove В§44 inequality | В§45 + val lemmas at В§46 + В§47 |\n"
"| Prove injectivity | В§48 + val lemmas at В§49 + В§50 + В§51 or В§52 |\n"
"| Identify as В§53 | В§54 |\n"
"| Find В§55 preimage | В§56 |\n"
"\n"
"**Where this is going**: In the next world (FinTuples), you'll use\n"
"В§57 to model tuples вҖ” ordered lists of fixed length.\n"
"The В§58/В§59 decomposition powers В§60 (adding at the front),\n"
"and the В§61/В§62 decomposition powers В§63 (adding at\n"
"the back)."
msgstr ""

