#: Game.Levels.FinsetImage.L10_ImageIntersectionCounterexample
msgid "You've proved that the containment В§0\n"
"can be **strict** when В§1 is not injective.\n"
"\n"
"**The phantom witness phenomenon**: The element В§2 in\n"
"В§3 is a **phantom** вҖ” it looks like it belongs to\n"
"the image of the intersection, but it doesn't. Why? Because the\n"
"witnesses that produce it are *different*: В§4 maps to В§5,\n"
"and В§6 maps to В§7, but В§8, so there's no single\n"
"element in В§9 that maps to В§10.\n"
"\n"
"**Why union works but intersection doesn't**: Compare the two results:\n"
"\n"
"- В§11 вҖ” **exact equality**, always.\n"
"- В§12 вҖ” **only containment** in general.\n"
"\n"
"For union, if В§13, the witness В§14 that maps to В§15\n"
"is in В§16 or В§17, so it's in В§18. No phantom is possible вҖ” the\n"
"single witness suffices.\n"
"\n"
"For intersection, В§19 gives you **two** witnesses:\n"
"В§20 and В§21 with В§22. Unless В§23 (which\n"
"injectivity guarantees), these witnesses are useless for proving\n"
"В§24.\n"
"\n"
"The structural reason: image is 'surjective onto its own elements' вҖ”\n"
"every element of В§25 has a preimage by definition. Union only needs\n"
"*existence* of a preimage (one witness anywhere), which image always\n"
"provides. Intersection needs a *shared* preimage (one witness in both\n"
"sets), which image can't guarantee without injectivity."
