#: Game.Levels.FinTuples.L19_FlippingEquations
msgid "# The .symm Suffix\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes you have an equation pointing the wrong way. If\n"
"В§0, you need В§1. The suffix **В§2** flips\n"
"an equation:\n"
"\n"
"> If В§3, then В§4.\n"
"\n"
"This works on any equation вҖ” it's the symmetry of equality.\n"
"\n"
"**Why does direction matter?** In Lean, В§5 is a\n"
"**directional** operation: if В§6, it replaces В§7 with\n"
"В§8 (left-to-right), never the reverse. So even though В§9\n"
"and В§10 are logically equivalent, В§11 and В§12\n"
"do different things. When a lemma gives you В§13 but you need\n"
"to replace В§14 with В§15, you must flip the equation with В§16\n"
"before rewriting.\n"
"\n"
"You already know two reconstruction identities:\n"
"- В§17\n"
"- В§18\n"
"\n"
"Both say 'reconstructed = original'. But often you need the\n"
"reverse direction: 'original = reconstructed'. That's where\n"
"В§19 comes in:\n"
"- В§20\n"
"- В§21\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove both reversed reconstruction identities."
msgstr ""

