#: Game.Levels.SummationFormulas.L13_SumComm
msgid "# Double Sums and the Order of Summation\n"
"\n"
"Imagine a grid of numbers вҖ” rows indexed by В§0, columns by В§1.\n"
"You can add up all the entries by going **row by row** (for each В§2,\n"
"sum over all В§3) or **column by column** (for each В§4, sum over\n"
"all В§5). Either way, you get the same total.\n"
"\n"
"This is **Fubini's principle for finite sums**: the order of\n"
"summation doesn't matter.\n"
"\n"
"В§6\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, this is В§7. Note that В§8 is completely\n"
"arbitrary вҖ” the function does NOT need to be symmetric in В§9 and В§10.\n"
"The result holds purely because addition is commutative and\n"
"associative.\n"
"\n"
"**Why this matters**: In combinatorics, **double counting** is the\n"
"technique of computing the same quantity two ways. One direction may\n"
"be easy while the other is hard, and equating them gives a non-obvious\n"
"identity. В§11 is the formal backbone of double counting вҖ” it\n"
"lets you switch from the hard direction to the easy one.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove the interchange directly using В§12\n"
"(learned in BigOpAlgebra)."
msgstr ""

