#: Game.Levels.BigOpAlgebra
msgid "# Big Operators: Algebraic Manipulation\n"
"\n"
"In the BigOpIntro world, you learned to unfold sums and products\n"
"over concrete finsets using В§0, В§1, and\n"
"В§2. Those are the *computational* tools вҖ” they let you\n"
"evaluate specific sums.\n"
"\n"
"This world teaches the *algebraic* tools вҖ” structural\n"
"transformations that manipulate sums without computing them:\n"
"\n"
"- **Linearity**: В§3\n"
"- **Products distribute**: В§4\n"
"- **Constant sums**: В§5\n"
"- **Constant products**: В§6\n"
"- **Union splitting**: В§7 (disjoint)\n"
"- **Filtering**: summing with a predicate guard\n"
"- **Double sum interchange**: В§8\n"
"- **Range peeling**: В§9\n"
"\n"
"You'll also learn two new proof-organization tools:\n"
"- **calc blocks** вҖ” chain multi-step equalities into readable proofs\n"
"- **ring** вҖ” automatically close algebraic rearrangements\n"
"\n"
"A key insight: **cardinality is summation of 1s**. The theorem\n"
"В§10 bridges counting and summation, and you'll\n"
"use it in both directions throughout this world.\n"
"\n"
"We focus primarily on the additive tools. Each additive identity\n"
"has a multiplicative twin (e.g., В§11 parallels\n"
"В§12), and you'll see these in the documentation вҖ” the\n"
"proofs are structurally identical. The multiplicative tools are\n"
"available in your toolbox for later use.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: Everything from BigOpIntro (В§13,\n"
"В§14, В§15, В§16, В§17)."
msgstr ""

