#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L24_DualDistributivity
msgid "You've proved the **dual distributivity** law:\n"
"В§0.\n"
"\n"
"Was it really 'the same proof pattern, swapping В§1 and В§2'?\n"
"Almost вҖ” the forward direction was parallel (case-split, rebuild\n"
"with В§3), but the backward direction required a\n"
"**nested case-split**: splitting on В§4, then conditionally\n"
"splitting on В§5. This asymmetry is the difference between\n"
"distributing В§6 over В§7 (needs one case-split) and\n"
"В§8 over В§9 (needs nested case-splits).\n"
"\n"
"Together, Levels 23 and 24 show that union and intersection distribute\n"
"over each other in both directions вҖ” this is the defining property\n"
"of a **distributive lattice**, a structure you'll revisit in the\n"
"orders and lattices course.\n"
"\n"
"**A deeper connection**: You proved both distributivity laws from\n"
"scratch using В§10 + logic. In fact, either one follows from the\n"
"other via De Morgan's law. De Morgan *dualizes* В§11 and В§12,\n"
"converting one distributivity law into the other. This means the\n"
"two laws are not independent вҖ” they're two faces of the same coin.\n"
"The proof-from-scratch approach is more instructive (it exercises\n"
"the logic directly), but the derivation via De Morgan shows the\n"
"structural economy underneath.\n"
"\n"
"**The duality principle**: Look back at the identities you've proved\n"
"in this world. They come in pairs:\n"
"\n"
"| Identity | Dual |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| В§13 | В§14 |\n"
"| В§15 | В§16 |\n"
"| В§17 | В§18 |\n"
"| В§19 | В§20 |\n"
"| В§21 | В§22 |\n"
"\n"
"The pattern: swap В§23 (equivalently,\n"
"В§24, or В§25),\n"
"and you get the dual identity. This is not a coincidence вҖ” it's a\n"
"theorem. In any **Boolean algebra** (and finsets form one), every\n"
"identity has a valid dual obtained by this swap. Once you prove\n"
"commutativity of В§26, you *know* commutativity of В§27 holds\n"
"by the same argument with the roles swapped.\n"
"\n"
"This duality is exactly what the lattice notation В§28/В§29\n"
"(Level 16) captures: the abstract lattice axioms are self-dual, so\n"
"every theorem about В§30 has a mirror theorem about В§31.\n"
"\n"
"Next: the boss, which integrates set difference with the\n"
"unfold-to-logic recipe."
msgstr ""

