#: Game.Levels.FinTuples.L01_FunctionsAsTuples
msgid "# Functions from Fin as Tuples\n"
"\n"
"In the previous worlds, you learned that В§0 is the type of\n"
"natural numbers less than В§1. Now comes a key insight:\n"
"\n"
"**A function В§2 is the same thing as an В§3-tuple** вҖ” an\n"
"ordered list of В§4 elements from В§5.\n"
"\n"
"Why? A function from В§6 is determined by three values:\n"
"what it returns at В§7, at В§8, and at В§9. Those three values, in\n"
"order, form a triple. Conversely, any triple В§10\n"
"defines a function В§11 by В§12.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, В§13 creates a function В§14 that\n"
"returns В§15 at index В§16, В§17 at index В§18, and В§19 at index В§20.\n"
"The В§21 prefix distinguishes this from a plain list вҖ” it's a\n"
"**vector** (a function from В§22), not a linked list.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Verify that the element at index 1 of В§23\n"
"is В§24. (Remember: indexing starts at 0.)"
