"\n"
"This proof used a pattern that deserves a name: the **value\n"
"reduction strategy for hypotheses**. When you have a hypothesis\n"
"В§9 about В§10 elements:\n"
"1. В§11 вҖ” reduce to values\n"
"2. В§12 вҖ” simplify to в„• arithmetic\n"
"3. В§13 вҖ” derive a contradiction or close the goal\n"
"\n"
"In Level 5, you used the goal-level version (rewrite the *goal*\n"
"to values, then В§14). Here you used the hypothesis-level\n"
"version (rewrite the *hypothesis* to values, then В§15). Both\n"
"are instances of the same idea: **reduce Fin reasoning to в„•\n"
"arithmetic, then let omega handle it**.\n"
"\n"
"Combined with the separation facts (next levels) and the\n"
"decompositions (later), this means В§16 is neatly\n"
"partitioned by these two embedding functions."
msgstr ""

