#: Game.Levels.Cardinality.L23_GeneralPigeonhole
msgid "The **general pigeonhole principle**: for ANY В§0, no injective\n"
"function from В§1 to В§2 exists.\n"
"\n"
"The proof was *identical* to Level 21 вҖ” the same three steps,\n"
"the same lemmas. The numbers changed from В§3 and В§4 to В§5\n"
"and В§6, but В§7 handles the arithmetic in both cases.\n"
"\n"
"This is the power of the cardinality approach: the proof doesn't\n"
"depend on the specific sizes. The PsetFin approach (exhaustive\n"
"case analysis) only worked for specific values вҖ” extending it to\n"
"В§8 would require checking 100! combinations.\n"
"The counting argument handles all sizes in four lines.\n"
"\n"
"**The pigeonhole principle in plain language**: if you put В§9\n"
"pigeons into В§10 holes, at least two pigeons must share a hole.\n"
"The counting argument: if each hole had at most one pigeon\n"
"(injectivity), you'd need at least В§11 holes, but only В§12\n"
"exist.\n"
"\n"
"**Connection to card_image_le**: The pigeonhole principle is really a\n"
"corollary of a fact you already know: В§13\n"
"applied to В§14. If В§15 were injective,\n"
"В§16 would give\n"
"В§17, but the image lives in В§18 so\n"
"В§19 by В§20 + В§21.\n"
"Contradiction. In other words, **pigeonhole IS the statement that\n"
"non-injective maps shrink image cardinality** вҖ” which is exactly\n"
"what В§22 bounds."
msgstr ""

