#: Game.Levels.Cardinality
msgid "# Cardinality: Counting Elements\n"
"\n"
"You've been building finsets, proving membership, computing unions and\n"
"intersections, and mapping functions over them. But you haven't yet\n"
"asked: **how many elements does a finset contain?**\n"
"\n"
"The answer is В§0 вҖ” the cardinality function. For any finset\n"
"В§1, the expression В§2 returns a natural number: the count of\n"
"elements in В§3.\n"
"\n"
"This world covers the **card_* lemma family** вҖ” the toolkit for\n"
"computing and reasoning about cardinalities:\n"
"\n"
"**Building up**:\n"
"- В§4: В§5\n"
"- В§6: В§7\n"
"- В§8: inserting a new element adds 1\n"
"- В§9: В§10\n"
"\n"
"**Taking apart**:\n"
"- В§11: erasing an element subtracts 1\n"
"\n"
"**Connecting**:\n"
"- В§12: positive cardinality вҶ” nonempty (both directions)\n"
"- В§13: zero cardinality вҶ” empty\n"
"\n"
"**Comparing**:\n"
"- В§14: subsets have smaller (or equal) cardinality\n"
"\n"
"**Combining**:\n"
"- В§15: the inclusion-exclusion formula\n"
"- В§16: simplified form for disjoint sets\n"
"- В§17: complement counting\n"
"- В§18: the multiplication principle\n"
"\n"
"**Deriving**:\n"
"- Why inclusion-exclusion holds вҖ” derived from disjoint union and\n"
"  complement counting\n"
"\n"
"**Applying**:\n"
"- The **abstract pigeonhole principle** via cardinality вҖ” proving\n"
"  that more inputs than outputs forces a collision, without any\n"
"  case analysis\n"
"- The **capstone theorem**: for finite types, injective iff\n"
"  surjective вҖ” the mathematical climax of Phases 1-3\n"
"\n"
"The proof pattern throughout: bring a card lemma into the context\n"
"with В§19, then use В§20 to handle the arithmetic.\n"
"\n"
"You already met В§21 and В§22 in the Image world.\n"
"This world develops the full toolkit."
msgstr ""

