#: Game.Levels.PsetFin.L17_Pigeonhole
msgid "You've proved the **pigeonhole principle** for В§0:\n"
"any function from a 3-element set to a 2-element set must have\n"
"a collision.\n"
"\n"
"The proof strategy was:\n"
"1. **Classify** each output as В§1 or В§2\n"
"2. **Compare** outputs at pairs of inputs\n"
"3. **Find** two inputs with the same output\n"
"\n"
"Every tool in this proof came from Phase 1:\n"
"- Case analysis on В§3 (MeetFin)\n"
"- Existential witnesses with В§4 (MeetFin)\n"
"- Inequality pattern В§5 (MeetFin)\n"
"- Rewriting with hypotheses (FinTuples)\n"
"\n"
"**The abstract pigeonhole principle**: This generalizes. For any\n"
"function В§6, there must exist В§7 with\n"
"В§8 and В§9. More inputs than outputs forces a\n"
"collision вҖ” always. The concrete proof here used exhaustive case\n"
"analysis, which doesn't scale: for В§10, you'd\n"
"need astronomical case splits. In the Finset worlds ahead, you'll\n"
"learn cardinality tools that prove pigeonhole for any В§11 in a\n"
"few lines.\n"
"\n"
"**The cardinality consequence**: If there were a collision-free\n"
"function from В§12 to В§13, we could embed a 3-element set\n"
"into a 2-element set вҖ” which is impossible. So В§14,\n"
"confirming that В§15 is genuinely 'larger than' В§16. More\n"
"importantly, the parameter В§17 in В§18 is *recoverable* from\n"
"the type: В§19 and В§20 can only be equivalent (have a\n"
"bijection between them) when В§21. This is what makes В§22\n"
"the canonical finite type вҖ” it uniquely represents 'a type with\n"
"exactly n elements.'"
msgstr ""

