"\n"
"В§0\n"
"\n"
"Why does it work? When you add В§1, elements in В§2\n"
"are counted twice вҖ” once in В§3 and once in В§4. Subtracting\n"
"В§5 corrects the double count.\n"
"\n"
"The Lean statement uses the additive form В§6\n"
"because natural number subtraction can lose information (it floors at 0).\n"
"The additive form is unconditionally true.\n"
"\n"
"**Name this proof strategy**: **collect-and-close**. You brought a\n"
"cardinality lemma into context with В§7, then let a decision\n"
"procedure (В§8) handle the arithmetic. The mathematical thinking\n"
"goes into choosing which lemma to apply; the arithmetic is mechanical.\n"
"\n"
"This pattern is not specific to cardinality вҖ” it appears throughout\n"
"the course: В§9 + В§10 for linear arithmetic, В§11 + В§12\n"
"for polynomial algebra, and В§13 + В§14 + В§15 for mixed cases\n"
"(you'll meet this variant in SummationFormulas). Wherever you see it,\n"
"the strategy is the same: **collect** the relevant facts into the\n"
"context, then **close** with a decision procedure.\n"
"\n"
"This identity generalizes. For three sets:\n"
"\n"
"В§16\n"
"\n"
"The alternating-sign pattern continues: for В§17 sets, there are\n"
"В§18 correction terms.\n"
"\n"
"**Connection to the partition identity**: In FinsetOperations you proved\n"
"В§19. Since В§20 and\n"
"В§21 are disjoint, В§22 вҖ” this is\n"
"complement counting (Level 16). Inclusion-exclusion follows: since\n"
"В§23 and this is also disjoint,\n"
"В§24.\n"
"The partition identity is the deeper fact; inclusion-exclusion is its\n"
"numerical consequence."
msgstr ""

