#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L16_LatticeNotation
msgid "# New Tactics: В§0 and В§1\n"
"\n"
"Before tackling the main topic, you need two new tactics:\n"
"\n"
"**В§2** replaces the current goal with a definitionally equal\n"
"statement. If the goal displays as В§3, you can write\n"
"В§4 and Lean accepts it because В§5 and В§6 are\n"
"the same operation. The goal's *meaning* is unchanged; only the\n"
"*notation* changes.\n"
"\n"
"**В§7** does the same for a hypothesis. If\n"
"В§8, then В§9 rewrites the\n"
"hypothesis to use В§10 notation instead.\n"
"\n"
"Both tactics work whenever the old and new expressions are\n"
"*definitionally equal* вҖ” the same value, just written differently.\n"
"\n"
"# Lattice Notation: вҠ” and вҠ“\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, finset union and intersection are implemented through the\n"
"**lattice** structure. This means you'll sometimes see alternative\n"
"notation in the infoview:\n"
"\n"
"- В§11 is the same as В§12 (lattice 'supremum' = union)\n"
"- В§13 is the same as В§14 (lattice 'infimum' = intersection)\n"
"\n"
"These are **exactly the same operations** вҖ” just different notation.\n"
"\n"
"**The problem**: В§15 matches В§16 but not В§17.\n"
"When lattice notation appears, you need to convert it first using\n"
"В§18 (for the goal) or В§19 (for hypotheses). After\n"
"converting, all the familiar membership lemmas work normally.\n"
"\n"
"You may also encounter В§20 in place of В§21 (lattice order = subset).\n"
"The same В§22/В§23 technique handles it.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Given В§24 (intersection via lattice notation),\n"
"prove В§25 (union via lattice notation)."
msgstr ""

