#: Game.Levels.BigOpAlgebra.L15_RingTactic
msgid "# ring: Closing Algebraic Goals\n"
"\n"
"After transforming sums with big-operator lemmas, you often end up\n"
"with a goal that is pure algebra вҖ” rearranging additions and\n"
"multiplications. The В§0 tactic closes such goals automatically.\n"
"\n"
"**What В§1 can do**:\n"
"- В§2 вң“\n"
"- В§3 вң“\n"
"- Commutativity, associativity, distributivity вң“\n"
"\n"
"**What В§4 cannot do**:\n"
"- Anything involving hypotheses (it only looks at the goal)\n"
"- Anything involving В§5, В§6, membership, or non-ring operations\n"
"\n"
"So В§7 complements the big-operator lemmas: the lemmas reduce\n"
"sum expressions to algebraic form, and В§8 closes the algebra.\n"
"\n"
"There is also В§9, which normalizes ring expressions without\n"
"necessarily closing the goal. Use В§10 when В§11 alone\n"
"doesn't close the goal but you want to simplify the algebra.\n"
"\n"
"**В§12 vs В§13**: You already know В§14 from earlier worlds.\n"
