#: Game.Levels.Fintype
msgid "# Fintype: Counting Elements of Finite Types\n"
"\n"
"You've spent several worlds counting elements of specific finsets вҖ”\n"
"using В§0, В§1, В§2, and other В§3\n"
"lemmas. But there's a deeper question: how many elements does an entire\n"
"**type** have?\n"
"\n"
"The answer is В§4 вҖ” a typeclass that says a type has finitely many\n"
"elements. When В§5 has a В§6 instance, you get:\n"
"- В§7 вҖ” the total number of elements\n"
"- В§8 вҖ” the finset of ALL elements\n"
"\n"
"## Why counting types matters\n"
"\n"
"Counting the elements of a type is the foundation of combinatorics in\n"
"Lean. Once you know В§9, you can:\n"
"- **Apply pigeonhole**: if В§10, there is no injection В§11\n"
"- **Detect bijections**: if В§12 and a map is injective,\n"
"  it must be surjective (and vice versa)\n"
"- **Classify finite structures**: two finite groups of the same prime\n"
"  order must be isomorphic\n"
"\n"
"The В§13 typeclass makes all of this machine-checkable.\n"
"\n"
"## The composition rules\n"
"\n"
"The power of В§14 is **composition**: if you know the cardinalities\n"
"of building blocks, you can compute the cardinality of anything built\n"
"from them:\n"
"\n"
"| Construction | Formula | Name |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| В§15 (product) | В§16 | Multiplication principle |\n"
"| В§17 (sum) | В§18 | Addition principle |\n"
"| В§19 (functions) | В§20 | Exponentiation principle |\n"
"| В§21 (subtype) | В§22 | Complement counting |\n"
"| В§23 (equivalence) | В§24 | Bijective counting |\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: Not every type is finite! The natural numbers В§25 have no\n"
"В§26 instance. В§27 would be a type error. Finiteness\n"
"is a property that must be established, not assumed."
msgstr ""

