#: Game.Levels.Fintype.L06_FinitenessMatters
msgid "# Why Finiteness Matters\n"
"\n"
"You've now learned all five composition rules:\n"
"\n"
"| Construction | Formula | Lemma |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| В§0 | В§1 | В§2 |\n"
"| В§3 | В§4 | В§5 |\n"
"| В§6 | В§7 | В§8 |\n"
"| В§9 | В§10 | В§11 |\n"
"| В§12 | В§13 | В§14 |\n"
"\n"
"But there's a catch: these rules only work for **finite types** вҖ” types\n"
"with a В§15 instance.\n"
"\n"
"Consider the natural numbers В§16. There are infinitely many functions\n"
"В§17 (for each natural number, independently choose В§18 or\n"
"В§19). The \"formula\" В§20 is meaningless because В§21\n"
"is undefined вҖ” В§22 has no В§23 instance. Writing В§24\n"
"in Lean is a type error.\n"
"\n"
"The В§25 constraint in the statement below is what makes the\n"
"counting valid. Without it, В§26 would be a type error.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that for any finite type В§27, the number of\n"
"functions from В§28 to В§29 is В§30. This combines\n"
"В§31 and В§32."
msgstr ""

