#: Game.Levels.Cardinality.L25_SurjectiveImpliesInjective
msgid "# The Converse Direction\n"
"\n"
"Level 24 proved: if В§0 is **injective**, then\n"
"В§1 (i.e., f is surjective).\n"
"\n"
"Now prove the converse: if В§2 is **surjective**, then\n"
"В§3.\n"
"\n"
"The proof uses the same key lemma вҖ” В§4 вҖ” but\n"
"the cardinality bound comes from a different source:\n"
"\n"
"- **Level 23** (injective direction): the image has exactly В§5\n"
"  elements because injectivity preserves cardinality.\n"
"- **This level** (surjective direction): В§6 is a subset of the\n"
"  image (because surjectivity means every element is hit), so\n"
"  В§7 gives В§8.\n"
"\n"
"The two directions together give the complete characterization:\n"
"for endofunctions on finite types, В§9 iff В§10\n"
"is injective iff В§11 is surjective.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that if В§12 is surjective,\n"
"then В§13."
msgstr ""

