#: Game.Levels.Powerset
msgid "# Powerset: All Subsets of a Set\n"
"\n"
"Given a finite set В§0, how many subsets does it have? What if you only\n"
"want subsets of a specific size?\n"
"\n"
"**Concrete motivation**: Imagine choosing toppings for a pizza from a\n"
"menu of В§1 items. Each topping is independently *in* or *out* вҖ” that\n"
"gives В§2 possible pizzas. If you want exactly В§3 toppings, there\n"
"are В§4 options. The powerset formalizes this: it is the\n"
"collection of all possible choices.\n"
"\n"
"The **powerset** В§5 is the collection of all subsets of В§6.\n"
"The key characterization: В§7 if and only if В§8.\n"
"\n"
"In this world you'll learn:\n"
"\n"
"- **В§9** and its membership lemma В§10\n"
"- **В§11**: a set with В§12 elements has В§13 subsets\n"
"- **В§14**: the subsets of В§15 with exactly В§16 elements\n"
"- **В§17**: the count of В§18-element subsets is В§19\n"
"\n"
"This connects the *set-theoretic* operation (listing subsets) to the\n"
"*combinatorial* numbers (binomial coefficients) that you studied in the\n"
"BinomialCoefficients world. There, В§20 was defined recursively\n"
"via Pascal's identity. Here, you'll see its **counting meaning**: it counts\n"
"the В§21-element subsets.\n"
"\n"
"**Prerequisites**: В§22 for subset reasoning, В§23 from\n"
"Cardinality, and В§24 identities from BinomialCoefficients."
msgstr ""

